268
00:17:01,513 --> 00:17:03,034
"Won an award for the clay figurine.

269
00:17:03,154 --> 00:17:03,794
Happy.

270
00:17:03,914 --> 00:17:06,033
Also keyed that dirty old man's car.

271
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:06,993
Even happier."

272
00:17:07,634 --> 00:17:08,993
Who's this 'dirty old man'?

273
00:17:10,473 --> 00:17:12,394
An art teacher
from an after-school cram school.

274
00:17:12,753 --> 00:17:14,513
He kept groping the female students.

275
00:17:15,434 --> 00:17:16,634
I used my house keys

276
00:17:17,154 --> 00:17:18,354
to scratch his crappy car

277
00:17:18,473 --> 00:17:19,634
with a huge line.

278
00:17:20,473 --> 00:17:21,753
He said to call the police.

279
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:23,914
I said, "Great, let's tell them

280
00:17:23,993 --> 00:17:25,954
how you've been harassing girls."

281
00:17:29,553 --> 00:17:30,954
Such righteousness since childhood.

282
00:17:35,394 --> 00:17:36,834
When you have no one to protect you,

283
00:17:37,914 --> 00:17:39,273
you naturally put on

284
00:17:39,273 --> 00:17:40,473
an intimidating front.

285
00:17:41,753 --> 00:17:43,073
If you're pampered,

286
00:17:44,473 --> 00:17:45,914
you can afford to be gracious.

287
00:17:47,154 --> 00:17:49,114
But when you only have yourself,

288
00:17:49,874 --> 00:17:51,473
you fight tooth and nail.

289
00:17:54,834 --> 00:17:55,634
What about now?

